Results.ReviewText:
Hi
Typical Gold Blend drinker for years until .....
To be honest, if I wanted a barista style coffee I would have bought the Nescafé barista style drink.
But I didn’t. I wanted an original Gold Blend coffee.
Nescafé, if you maintain your sales figures with the new style drink, well done - a good gamble.
If you don’t, I hope you revert back to the old recipe before I find an acceptable equivalent from a competitor and another long term customer lost for good.
The very low number of comments here doesn’t truly reflect the upset around the world on the change, as voiced in many other Internet forums!
Results.Title: New style is not the drink I wanted

ClientResponses.Response: Thank you very much for taking the time & letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've made. We value your feedback & will be passing your comments to the wider team.

Results.ReviewText: New recipe is awful, i have drank nothing but this brand for 25 years but the new 'improved recipe' is horrible. the sludge at bottom of each cup is very off putting. If i wanted filtered coffee i would buy it, the reason us loyal customers purchased this upmarket instant coffee is because we liked it. Already trying out new brands!
Results.Title: Horrendouos

ClientResponses.Response: Thank you very much for getting in touch & leaving your feedback on the new recipe. We're sad to hear you're not a fan but really appreciate you letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: This was my preferred brand for years but you have destroyed that by adding ground coffee. A good cup of instant can be enjoyed to the last sip not leave a mouth full of sludge. The flavour seems to have suffered too. Why do you think pod  machines are so popular? Nobody wants residue in their drink.
Results.Title: Ruined

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for getting in touch. Due to the addition of micro ground coffee during the recent change there may be a residue at the bottom of your cup. Micro ground coffee is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: What did you do to the blend when you changed the packaging? It's now got sediment in the bottom, bits floating on top and tastes bitter..  are you filtering it through a sock.  Shouldn't have messed with perfection.
Results.Title: Bring back the old Nescafe Gold Blend
